Colonial <unclear/>
Sierra Leone 14 April 1879

Sir

In reply to your leter of the just relative to Charles Thompson and henry Miller who were under treatment in hospital in October last, I have to infrom you that they were suffering from fever of the ordinary type.

I am, Sir
Your obedient servant
W. Hwrm Haul
Colonial Surgeon

A Parm Esq
Consul